findings.lung_bases: no acute abnormality, no consolidation or effusion, no pulmonary nodules or masses identified
findings.liver: normal in size, contour and attenuation, no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilation
findings.kidneys: enhance symmetrically with symmetric contrast excretion, bilateral extrarenal pelves without hydronephrosis, single 7-mm hypodense lesion in the interpolar region of the right kidney, too small to characterize, no concerning renal mass lesions
findings.GI_tract: stomach, duodenum, and loops of small bowel are normal, no free fluid or free air in the abdomen
findings.vascular_system: normal caliber aorta, major mesenteric vessels patent
findings.appendix: appears normal but does not fill with contrast, tip is dilated and fluid-filled with mucosal hyperenhancement, measures up to 10 mm
